            '# Hi, I\'m Jonathan Verdun 👋\n\n> **Quality Architect | Senior QA Automation Engineer | Bioinformatics Researcher**\n>\n> I build deterministic, high-coverage testing ecosystems and resilient CI/CD infrastructures. My engineering philosophy is rooted in scientific discipline and shift-left logic.\n\n---\n\n### 🛡️ Quality Engineering Philosophy\n\nI don\'t just "test" software; I design **Quality Gates** that ensure technical and business requirements are met deterministically.\n\n- **100% Logic Coverage:** I maintain a strict 100% statement and branch coverage threshold on all core domain logic.\n- **Shift-Left Integration:** QA starts at the requirements phase, preventing defects through contract and API validation.\n- **Deep Resilience:** I implement fail-safe mechanisms (like WebGL fallbacks and offline PWA support) to ensure UX stability under any conditions.\n- **Automated Security:** Security audits (npm audit, secret scanning) are integrated directly into the CI pipeline.\n\n---\n\n### 🛠️ Tech Stack & Specialized Expertise\n\n- **Automation:** Playwright, Pytest, Appium, Jest, fast-check (Property-Based).\n- **Strategy:** Risk-Based Testing, Test Planning, Defect Lifecycle Management (ADO/Jira).\n- **Core Dev:** TypeScript, React, Python, FastAPI, C++.\n- **DevOps:** GitHub Actions (Hardened Pipelines), Docker, Nginx, CI Caching.\n- **A11y:** WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance (automated axe-core scans).\n\n---\n\n### 🔬 Research & Projects\n\n- **[Portfolio Implementation](https://github.com/gesttaltt/jonathan-verdun-portfolio):** A reference implementation of my QA mindset. Hardened to the extreme with PWA support, fail-safe fallbacks, and 100% coverage verified in CI.\n- **Bioinformatics:** Applying p-adic metric spaces and hyperbolic VAEs to viral sequence analysis, ensuring numerical stability in large-scale genomic pipelines.\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Professional Metrics (Live)\n\n| Category            | Status           | Verification Method       |\n| :------------------ | :--------------- | :------------------------ |\n| **Logic Coverage**  | `100%`           | Jest + Istanbul Gate      |\n| **A11y Compliance** | `WCAG 2.1 AA`    | CI axe-core scans         |\n| **Pipeline Status** | `Locked & Green` | Hardened GitHub Actions   |\n| **Security State**  | `Audited`        | `npm audit` High-Sev Gate |\n\n---\n\n### 📫 Connect with me\n\n- **Portfolio:** [jonathanverdun.com](https://jonathanverdun.com)\n- **LinkedIn:** [linkedin.com/in/jonathan-verdun](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathan-verdun/)\n- **Email:** [jonathan.verdun707@gmail.com](mailto:jonathan.verdun707@gmail.com)\n\n---\n\n_"Quality is not an act, it is a habit. In software, it must be a deterministic gate."_\n',
