            "# Portfolio Audit — 2026-04-30 (Post-H4 Refactor)\n\n**Project:** jonathan-verdun-portfolio  \n**Stack:** Next.js 16.1.6 · React 19.2.3 · TypeScript 5 · Tailwind 4 · Three.js 0.183  \n**Auditor:** Claude Sonnet 4.6  \n**Basis:** Full source read after H4 route-groups refactor (commit b26872b)  \n**Previous audit:** `docs/audit-2026-04-30.md` — all criticals and most highs resolved  \n**Build status:** ✓ passing · **Type check:** ✓ clean · **Tests:** 159/159 ✓\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThe H4 refactor (route groups for per-language `html[lang]`) introduced a small but meaningful\nset of new gaps, primarily in the Spanish route group's metadata completeness. Separately, a\nfull cross-codebase sweep surfaced additional findings across SEO, i18n parity, coverage\nhygiene, and a handful of UX and code quality items.\n\nNo new criticals. One high (ES layout metadata incomplete — a direct by-product of H4). The\nrest are medium-to-low polish and correctness issues.\n\n**Overall score: 9.3 / 10**  \n_(↑ from 9.1 — H4 `html[lang]` gap closed; one new High from ES layout gaps)_\n\n**Findings this cycle:** 0 critical · 2 high · 7 medium · 10 low\n\n---\n\n## Coverage Snapshot (2026-04-30, post-H4)\n\n```\nAll files   |   Stmts   |  Branch  |  Funcs  |  Lines\n------------|-----------|----------|---------|--------\nAll files   |   84.52 % |  90.90 % | 93.05 % | 86.17 %\n```\n\n> ⚠ The apparent dip from 96 % (previous audit) to 84.52 % is a **coverage-config gap**:\n> `src/app/robots.ts` is not in the `collectCoverageFrom` exclusion list and reports 0 % (it is a\n> server-only Next.js route, identical in nature to the already-excluded `sitemap.ts`). Fix is M2\n> below. Component and library coverage remains at or near 100 %.\n\n**Notable uncovered lines (excluding excluded files):**\n\n| File                   | Lines  | Reason                                                  |\n| ---------------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `Terminal.tsx`         | 27, 63 | `scrollRef.current` guard; `entry.id ?? index` fallback |\n| `animations.ts`        | 26     | `staggerItemVariants` default-param branch              |\n| `LanguageSelector.tsx` | 8      | `usePathname() ?? '/'` null-fallback branch             |\n| `lib/i18n/context.tsx` | 12     | same null-fallback as above                             |\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### HIGH\n\n---\n\n#### H1 — `(es)/layout.tsx` metadata incomplete after H4 split\n\n**Severity:** High  \n**File:** `src/app/(es)/layout.tsx:13-24`\n\nThe Spanish root layout introduced by H4 is missing `alternates` (hreflang links), a `twitter`\ncard block, and has a reduced `openGraph` config compared to the English layout. This causes\nSpanish routes to emit no `<link rel=\"alternate\">` hreflang tags and no Twitter card metadata,\nharming both SEO and social sharing.\n\n**Missing from ES layout vs EN layout:**\n\n```ts\n// MISSING:\nalternates: {\n  canonical: `${siteConfig.url}/es/`,\n  languages: { en: siteConfig.url, es: `${siteConfig.url}/es/` },\n},\n// MISSING:\ntwitter: {\n  card: 'summary_large_image',\n  title: '...',\n  description: '...',\n  creator: siteConfig.socialLinks.twitter.handle,\n},\n// INCOMPLETE openGraph — missing url, images\n```\n\n**Fix:** Add the missing fields to `(es)/layout.tsx`. Also consider extracting a\n`buildBaseMetadata(lang)` factory in `src/lib/metadata.ts` to keep both layouts in sync going\nforward (see M1).\n\n---\n\n#### H2 — Boot sequence `help` output lists fewer commands than are actually available\n\n**Severity:** High  \n**File:** `src/lib/contracts/TerminalContract.ts:29` and `src/lib/i18n/es.ts:166`\n\n`BOOT_COMMANDS[2].output` (English) says:\n\n```\nAvailable commands: help, about, projects, contact, clear\n```\n\nBut `INTERACTIVE_COMMANDS` exposes `help, about, projects, research, contact, clear` (including\n`ls projects` as an alias). The boot output actively lies about what the terminal can do — `research`\nand `ls projects` are silently omitted. The Spanish boot sequence has the same problem (`ayuda`\noutput on boot says 5 commands; `interactive.ayuda` lists 6).\n\n**Fix:**\n\n```ts\n// TerminalContract.ts — boot help output must match interactive help output:\noutput: 'Available commands: help, about, projects, research, ls projects, contact, clear',\n```\n\nAnd in `es.ts`:\n\n```ts\noutput: 'Comandos disponibles: ayuda, sobre, proyectos, investigacion, ls proyectos, contacto, limpiar',\n```\n\n---\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n---\n\n#### M1 — Metadata duplicated across EN and ES layouts — no shared factory\n\n**Severity:** Medium  \n**File:** `src/app/(en)/layout.tsx:13-39` · `src/app/(es)/layout.tsx:13-24`\n\n`metadataBase`, `authors`, `creator` are copy-pasted into both layouts. Any change (e.g. new\n`siteConfig` field, added OG image) must be made in two places. After fixing H1, the duplication\nsurface grows further.\n\n**Fix:** Create `src/lib/metadata.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport function buildMetadata(lang: 'en' | 'es'): Metadata { ... }\n```\n\nBoth layouts call `export const metadata = buildMetadata('en')` / `buildMetadata('es')`.\n\n---\n\n\n\n[Content truncated...]",
